I"<p>People are capable of adjusting their baseline reference point of pain and pleasure based on experience. This means that through long enough exposure to a pleasant or painful stimuli, one is going to eventually <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perception-is-context-dependent">perceive it as perfectly ordinary</a>. The notion of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/apathy-is-hedonic-adaptation-to-dreadful-situations">hedonic adaptation empowers individuals going through difficult situations</a>.</p>
